ctsmtmibRingTable.name: ctsmtmibRingTable
ctsmtmibRingTable.description: A list of fddi nodes found on the ring.

ctsmtmibRingEntry.name: ctsmtmibRingEntry
ctsmtmibRingEntry.description: A fddi ring entry containing information common to all stations in a token path.

ctsmtmibRingSmtIndex.name: ctsmtmibRingSmtIndex
ctsmtmibRingSmtIndex.description: The value of the SMT index associated with this ring.

ctsmtmibRingMacIndex.name: ctsmtmibRingMacIndex
ctsmtmibRingMacIndex.description: A unique value for each MAC within a given SMT.

ctsmtmibRingNodeIndex.name: ctsmtmibRingNodeIndex
ctsmtmibRingNodeIndex.description: The index of the node on the ring in reverse token flow order. It is sequential from 1 to n where n is the number of nodes on the ring at a given time.

ctsmtmibRingMacAddr.name: ctsmtmibRingMacAddr
ctsmtmibRingMacAddr.description: A canonical representation of the MAC address of the node.

ctsmtmibRingUpStreamAddr.name: ctsmtmibRingUpStreamAddr
ctsmtmibRingUpStreamAddr.description: This is a canonical representation of the upstream neighbor's address. The upstream neighbor is the last MAC to receive the token before this MAC. Unknown addresses should be specified as 00-00-F8-00-00-00.

ctsmtmibRingNodeClass.name: ctsmtmibRingNodeClass
ctsmtmibRingNodeClass.description: Reports if the node is a station or a concentrator.

ctsmtmibRingMacCount.name: ctsmtmibRingMacCount
ctsmtmibRingMacCount.description: The number of MACs on this FDDI node.

ctsmtmibRingNonMasterCount.name: ctsmtmibRingNonMasterCount
ctsmtmibRingNonMasterCount.description: The sum of all A ports, B ports, and S ports on this node.

ctsmtmibRingMasterCount.name: ctsmtmibRingMasterCount
ctsmtmibRingMasterCount.description: The number of master ports on this node.

ctsmtmibRingTopology.name: ctsmtmibRingTopology
ctsmtmibRingTopology.description: A bit mapped representation of the current state of the node. if state: Add 2**n where n = Wrapped Node 0 Unattached Concentrator 1 A-A Twisted Ring 2 B-B Twisted Ring 3 Rooted Station 4 SRF Supported 5 where Wrapped Node: is set when the node's cf-state is Wrap-A, Wrap-B, Wrap-C, or Wrap-AB. Unattached Concentrator: is set when a concentrator has no active A, B, or S ports. A-A Twisted Ring: is set when this node's A port is connected to another A port. B-B Twisted Ring: is set when this node's B port is connected to another B port. Rooted Station: is a station with ports A, B and S, not active in tree mode. SRF Supported: This node adheres to the status reporting frame protocol.

ctsmtmibRingDuplicate.name: ctsmtmibRingDuplicate
ctsmtmibRingDuplicate.description: A bit mapped representation of duplicate address information. if State: Add 2**n where n= My Duplicate: 0 UNA Duplicate: 1 where My Duplicate: This node determines that it's MAC address is same as the MAC address for another node on the ring. UNA Duplicate: The upstream neighbor of this node has determined that its's MAC address is same as the MAC address for another node on the ring.

ctsmtmibMacTable.name: ctsmtmibMacTable
ctsmtmibMacTable.description: A list of MAC entries. The total number of entries is given by the value of ctsmtmibRingMacCount with appropriate ctsmtmibRingMacAddr.

ctsmtmibMacEntry.name: ctsmtmibMacEntry
ctsmtmibMacEntry.description: A MAC entry containing information pertaining to a given MAC.

ctsmtmibMacSmtIndex.name: ctsmtmibMacSmtIndex
ctsmtmibMacSmtIndex.description: The value of the SMT Index associated with this MAC.

ctsmtmibMacIndex.name: ctsmtmibMacIndex
ctsmtmibMacIndex.description: A unique value for each MAC within a given SMT.

ctsmtmibMacNifTxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacNifTxCts
ctsmtmibMacNifTxCts.description: The count of Neighborhood Information frames transmitted by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacNifRxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacNifRxCts
ctsmtmibMacNifRxCts.description: The count of Neighborhood Information frames received by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacSifTxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacSifTxCts
ctsmtmibMacSifTxCts.description: The count of Status Information frames transmitted by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacSifRxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacSifRxCts
ctsmtmibMacSifRxCts.description: The count of Status Information Frames received by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacEcfTxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacEcfTxCts
ctsmtmibMacEcfTxCts.description: The count of Echo Frames transmitted by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacEcfRxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacEcfRxCts
ctsmtmibMacEcfRxCts.description: The count of Echo Frames received by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacPmfTxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacPmfTxCts
ctsmtmibMacPmfTxCts.description: The count of Parameter Management Frames transmitted by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacPmfRxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacPmfRxCts
ctsmtmibMacPmfRxCts.description: The count of Parameter Management Frames received by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacRdfTxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacRdfTxCts
ctsmtmibMacRdfTxCts.description: The count of Request Denied Frames transmitted by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacRdfRxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacRdfRxCts
ctsmtmibMacRdfRxCts.description: The count of Request Denied Frames received by the MAC.

ctsmtmibMacRingOpCts.name: ctsmtmibMacRingOpCts
ctsmtmibMacRingOpCts.description: The count of the number of times the ring has entered 'Ring Operational' state from the 'Ring Not Operational' state.

ctsmtmibMacTxCts.name: ctsmtmibMacTxCts
ctsmtmibMacTxCts.description: A count that should as closely as possible match the number of frames transmitted by this MAC.

ctsmtmibMacRingMapUpdateCts.name: ctsmtmibMacRingMapUpdateCts
ctsmtmibMacRingMapUpdateCts.description: The count of the number of times the ring map table has been updated.

ctsmtmibMacAutoNegotiation.name: ctsmtmibMacAutoNegotiation
ctsmtmibMacAutoNegotiation.description: Indicates whether the station has auto-negotiation enabled or disabled.

ctsmtmibAttachmentNumber.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentNumber
ctsmtmibAttachmentNumber.description: The total number of attachments (across all SMTs) on this network management application entity. The value for this variable must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ctsmtmibAttachmentTable.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentTable
ctsmtmibAttachmentTable.description: A list of Attachment entries. The number of entries is given by the value of fdmimAttachmentNumber.

ctsmtmibAttachmentEntry.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentEntry
ctsmtmibAttachmentEntry.description: An Attachment entry containing information common to a given set of Attachments. There is a natural association of Attachment resource indices to the PORT Indices. The resource index for the Attachment is equal to the associated port index for 'single-attachment' and 'concentrator' type fdmimAttachmentClasses. For 'dual-attachment' classes, the Attachment Index is the PORT Index of the A PORT of the A/B PORT pair that represents the Attachment.

ctsmtmibAttachmentSMTIndex.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentSMTIndex
ctsmtmibAttachmentSMTIndex.description: The value of the SMT index associated with this Attachment.

ctsmtmibAttachmentIndex.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentIndex
ctsmtmibAttachmentIndex.description: A unique value for each Attachment on a given SMT.

ctsmtmibAttachmentClass.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentClass
ctsmtmibAttachmentClass.description: The Attachment class. This represents a PORT or a pair of PORTs plus the associated optional optical bypass that are managed as a functional unit. The PORT associations are the following unit. single-attachment - S Ports dual-attachment - A/B Port pairs concentrator - M Ports

ctsmtmibAttachmentOpticalBypassPresent.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentOpticalBypassPresent
ctsmtmibAttachmentOpticalBypassPresent.description: The value of this is false for 'single-attachment' . Correct operation of CMT for single-attachments requires that a bypass function must not loopback the network side of the MIC, but only the node side.

ctsmtmibAttachmentIMaxExpiration.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentIMaxExpiration
ctsmtmibAttachmentIMaxExpiration.description: I_Max (refer to ANSI SMT 9.4.4.2.1). Systems not implementing optical bypass should return a value of 0. Else the value should be returned in the granularity of 80ns.

ctsmtmibAttachmentInsertedStatus.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentInsertedStatus
ctsmtmibAttachmentInsertedStatus.description: Indicates whether the attachment is currently inserted in the node.

ctsmtmibAttachmentInsertPolicy.name: ctsmtmibAttachmentInsertPolicy
ctsmtmibAttachmentInsertPolicy.description: Indicates the Insert Policy for this Attachment.

ctsmtmibSMTTable.name: ctsmtmibSMTTable
ctsmtmibSMTTable.description: Describes the dual homed status for SMT entries.

ctsmtmibSMTEntry.name: ctsmtmibSMTEntry
ctsmtmibSMTEntry.description: A specific dual homed SMT entry.

ctsmtmibSMTDualHomeStatus.name: ctsmtmibSMTDualHomeStatus
ctsmtmibSMTDualHomeStatus.description: Indicates the current dual homed link status for a given SMT instance. notDualHomed(1) - This SMT is not dual homed. linkAorB(2) - Dual homed with link on A and no link link on B, or link on B and no link on A. linkAandB(3) - Dual homed with link on A and B.

ctsmtmibSMTDualHomeWrpLEDStatus.name: ctsmtmibSMTDualHomeWrpLEDStatus
ctsmtmibSMTDualHomeWrpLEDStatus.description: When on, the WRAP LED will be illuminated when the node is in a dual homed configuration with link on the A, B or both A and B ports. When off, the WRAP LED will not be illuminated when the node is in a dual homed configuration with link on A and B, but will be illuminated when in a dual homed configuration with no link on A or B.
